Dear Emacs, please make this -*-Text-*- mode!

NEWS for gWidgetsWWW2

Changes for 0.5-1
-------------------

* Replace Reference Classes by R6 classes in the hope to improve speed

* Remove some stuff that seems hard to maintain (could be added again later):
  ggooglemaps, Apache related things, load_dir and load_dirapp

* Remove examples that are currently not working

Changes for 0.4-6
-------------------

* Make it possible to have less than 5 panels in gborderlayout

Changes for 0.4-5
-------------------

* Adapt load_app.R to work with R 3.2.0


Changes for 0.4-4
-------------------

* Sync master branch to r-forge for automatic building of packages for all platforms


Changes for 0.4-3
-------------------

* DESCRIPTION: added copyright and licensing information, added Johannes Ranke as a contributor

* Some fixes in roxygen documentation and addressing R CMD check complaints


Changes for 0.4-2
-------------------

* Comment out the "Transport process" messages to the terminal

* gWidgets-app.R: Use appenv environment instead of .GlobalEnv

* gWidgets-app.R: Don't detach the environment "e" after loading the script

* gWidgets-app.R: Change port number

* Include download_extjs function to make it possible to ship without ExtJS


Changes for 0.4-1
-------------------

* Make R package exclude many unnecessary files from ExtJS by use of .Rbuildignore


Changes for 0.4-0
-------------------

* Remove canvas widget as the R package appears to be unmaintained

* make extjs load through a cdn. No longer include code. Re-add code later to be independent of an active internet connection

* add in comments about gWidgetsWWW2.rapache, deprecate other deployments
  of gWidgetsWWW2 beyond Rook.

Changes for 0.3
-------------------

* make extjs load through a cdn. No longer include code

* add in comments about gWidgetsWWW2.rapache, deprecate other deployments
  of gWidgetsWWW2 beyond Rook.

Changes for 0.3
-------------------


* now use Ext-4.1-beta-2. 

* We use Ext-4.1-beta so that certain layouts work. A **major
  drawback** is the fact that it doesn't work with IE! Oh well, try
  chrome for now. When 4.1 is out of beta it should be back to normal

* New widgets: gstackwidget, gpanel, gborderlayout, gcodemirror

* Major changes to integrate in Ext-4.0.

* move to GitHub for development

Changes for 0.1
-------------------

* Initial release
